title: For Sale:  COP .357 Derrenger (4 Barrel)
postcontent:
COP (Compact Off-Duty Police) .357 Derringer. Very Good to excellent condition. I have put 8 rounds through the gun. Comes with owners manual, box and outer sleeve.
$1000 firm, not interested in trades, cash only. Will only accept calls at 505-4 zero 1-7391. NO TEXT MESSAGES. Thx

The COP 357 is a 4 shot Derringer type pistol chambered for the powerful .357 Magnum round. It was designed by Robert Hillberg, based on his earlier work on the Hillberg Insurgency Weapon. It was manufactured by the now defunct COP Inc. of 3040 West Lomita Blvd., Torrance, California (COP stood for Compact Off-Duty Police). The double action weapon is only slightly larger than the typical .25 automatic pistol, which made it a good choice for a defensive weapon or a police backup gun.

The COP 357 is quite robust in design and construction. It is made of solid stainless steel components. Cartridges are loaded into the four separate chambers by sliding a latch that "pops-up" the barrel for loading purposes, similar to top-break shotguns. Each of the four chambers has its own dedicated firing pin. It uses an internal hammer, which is activated by depressing the trigger to hit a ratcheting/rotating striker that in turn strikes one firing pin at a time. Older "pepperboxes" also used multiple barrels, but the barrels were the part that rotated. The COP 357 operates similarly to the Sharps rimfire pepperbox of the 1850s, in that it uses the ratcheting/rotating striker, which is completely internal, to fire each chamber in sequence.

The weapon has appeared in numerous films, including Blade Runner, The Matrix Reloaded, and Bad Boys. It was also used by Carlton Lassiter in Psych in "Heeeeere's Lassie" (Season 6, Episode 11).

title: For Sale/Trade:  Manurhin Walther PP, 1955, .32, 7.65 cal, C&R with two original mags, Excellent
location: Fort Thomas, KY near Cincinnati, Northern Kentucky, Kentucky
postcontent: In excellent condition, made by Manurhin under license from Walther. Originally used by the Bavarian Police.  Serial number dates it to 1955 or 1956, so it's C&R eligible and I will ship.   Interarms had an exclusive US import contract with Walther until some time in the early 1980's.  Manurhin was the French manufacturer of Walther's until Walther established their own plant (their previous factory being in East Germany).  At some point Manurhin attempted to import these to the US, Interarms sued and the result was what you see--a Manurhin licensed Walther with the "Walther" scrubbed from both slide & grips. An interesting transitional model.  In excellent shape with two original Manurhin marked mags.  I have disassembled, cleaned, lubed and test fired this gun, and it runs as good as it looks.

title: For Sale/Trade:  Mega Arms MATEN KeyMod 308/7.62mm AR-10
postcontent:
For sale is a Mega Arms MATEN build using their MKM KeyMod upper and original non-ambi lower receiver set.  Barrel is an 18 inch Black Hole Weaponry stainless 308B barrel capable of shooting  7.62 NATO and 308 Winchester.  It uses polygonal rifling with a 1x11 twist rate and mid length gas system.  Barrel has been dimpled by Marvin Pitts of Nefarious Arms to shave some weight.  It's a work of art.  Flash hider is an AR Performance Slim Twisted model that's the same diameter as the barrel.  Again, a slight weight saver.  Gas block is an SLR Rifleworks Sentry 7 adjustable model.  It makes for a very smooth, light recoiling 308.  Bolt is a JP Enterprises Super Bolt and the carrier is a chromed DPMS standard carrier with staked chromed key.  Charging handle is a BCM Gunfighter with large latch for better leverage.  Lower parts is a standard DPMS 308 parts kit but the trigger was sent off to Bill Springfield of Colorado Springs for one of his fantastic trigger jobs.  Breaks neat and clean but not sure about the weight.  I paid for the 4.5lb trigger but don't have a way to measure it.  It's nice.  Receiver extension is Vltor with Vltor sling endplate and staked castle nut.  Stock is Magpul MOE SL again to save some weight.  It fits so snug and is so comfortable this will the be the stock I'll use on future builds.  Buffer is an H3 and the recoil spring is factory Armalite per Mega Arms' recommendation.  Extra spring included in sale.  Ejection port cover was engraved with caliber by Ident Marking Service.  The pistol grip contains a small parts repair kit and extra firing pin.  According to two scales in my house unloaded weight comes in right at 9 pounds.
   Round count is about 350 to 400 rounds and there have been no problems besides a bad magazine.  If you do your part this rifle is capable of sub-MOA accuracy.
  The Daniel Defense sights and sling are NOT included.  Does include one 20 and 25 round Magpul mags.

I'm asking $1545 or trades.
